## What this does
Builds a generator + Makefile target + CI integration that produces
`docs/REFERENCE.md` from live signals, so future debugging sessions can
grep one file instead of hunting through code each time.

The reference covers six sections, all extracted programmatically (no
hand-maintained drift):

1. **DB schema** — every user table from Postgres, columns, indexes, FKs
2. **Auth state per endpoint** — every `@router.<verb>` decorator in `api/routers/`,
   classified as auth-required or public based on `Depends(get_current_user)` presence
3. **WebSocket event types** — every distinct `manager.broadcast({"type": ...})`
   value the GUI consumes, with the source file/line
4. **Log channels** — short hand-maintained section explaining where each
   log type goes (stdout vs operation_log table vs WS vs Prometheus vs DB tables)
5. **Prometheus counter inventory** — every `Counter(...)` and `Gauge(...)` from
   `api/metrics.py` with name + labels + description
6. **Common diagnostic SQL queries** — pre-baked, named blocks for typical questions
   (latest test runs, failures by category, ops with no tool calls, harness fires,
   facts coverage, agent_attempts populated ratio, etc.)

The generator runs against the LIVE postgres instance for section 1 (so it
reflects whatever migrations have run, including module-managed tables not
in `api/db/models.py`), and against the source tree for sections 2/3/5
(AST-walked).

Sections 4 and 6 are hand-maintained markdown templates the generator
wraps into the output unchanged.

